Business Brief -- Philadelphia Electric Co.:
   Company Is Fined by NRC
   For Safety Code Violations
A spokesman for Philadelphia Electric said the King of
Prussia, Pa., company has agreed to pay the fine, but added
that the violations of NRC regulations never constituted a
hazard to public safety. "At no time was the plant in a
condition that would have prevented a safe shutdown," the
spokesman said. "Over the past two years, progress was made
at improving the performance of the Peach Bottom plants."